From 3c35fe9f12b1662ac047c929205eecbb902b458b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ramesh Mandal <ramesh@6epixels.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 02:38:33 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(m8): communities, profile editor, contact info, emoji,
 animations

Server (17/17 privacy tests):
- communities: create (admin), consent-gated invites restricted to the
  admin's ACCEPTED connections, accept joins + notifies members,
  decline/leave notifies admin with attempts left, 3-strike bar is
  permanent per community; group messages relayed to online members
  only, zero retention; private members receive nothing
- profile photo (small data URL, capped) carried through hello/roster

Extension:
- Communities tab: Groups | Discover segments, create community,
  invite consent cards (attempt counter shown), invite badge on tab
- community chats in Inbox: group icon, author names/colors on bubbles
- InfoPanel (tap chat header): peer public details (username, real
  name, photo, presence, connection status) or community members with
  admin invite manager; shared links list; mute, clear history
  (device-local), block/unblock, report, leave community
- Contacts rule: strictly accepted connections you've actually chatted
  with (demo contacts exempt)
- Settings profile editor: display name, avatar color, photo upload
  (canvas-compressed ~96px), changes reannounced live; message
  animations toggle
- emoji picker in composer; iMessage-style spring pop animations via
  framer-motion (respects the toggle)
- chat store: conversation kinds (dm/community) with persist migration,
  mute list persisted, clear history
